                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text">
                    <div class="info-box-paragraph">
                        <i>Deinagkistrodon</i>: dein is derived from the Greek 'deinos', which means 'terrible' and was "chosen in reference to the fear and awe with which this snake is held in many parts of its range <i>(1)</i>; <i>agkistrodon</i> is derived from the Greek words "agkistron", meaning "fishhook", and "odon", meaning "tooth", a reference to the curved fangs.
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-box-paragraph">
                        <i>Acutus</i> means "sharp, pointed", a reference to the pointy nose.
                    </div>
                    The Chinese name <span lang="zh-TW">百步蛇</span> (bai3bu4she2) means "Hundred Pace Snake".
                </div>
            </div>
